5 Section 1. R.S. 15:933.2 is hereby enacted to read as follows:
6 §933.2. Office of juvenile justice; annual report to the legislature
7 The secretary of the office of juvenile justice shall submit an annual
8 report on or before February first of each year to the Senate Committee on
9 Judiciary B, the House Committee on Administration of Criminal Justice, and
10 the David R. Poynter Legislative Research Library pursuant to R.S. 24:771 and
11 772. The report shall, at a minimum, include the following information:
12 (1) Prevention and intervention programs available to juveniles,
13 including school and community-based programs.
14 (2) Development of diversion programs with expanded eligibility.
15 (3) For juveniles in the custody of the office of juvenile justice, access to
16 educational resources and physical and mental health resources, including but
17 not limited to assessments and treatment.
18 (4)(a) The number of juveniles in the custody of the office of juvenile
19 justice delineated by age of juvenile and facility.
20 (b) The number of complaints received by the office of juvenile justice
21 from a juvenile in the custody of the office or his family delineated by type of
22 complaint and facility.
